verbose_text: RP mice injected with recombinant adenoviruses driving Cre expression, either ubiquitously (Ad5-CMV-Cre) or specifically in CGRP POS, K14 POS, SPC POS, and CC10 POS lung cells, consistently and exclusively developed NE lesions with the typical central SCLC as the most pronounced lesion, although the latency, penetrance, and number of lesions per mouse ranged from high (CMV) to low (CC10) (XREF_FIG; XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY, and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
